						               													<description>Equipment consists of a 7x7 board and watermelon shaped pieces in Green and Red. There are 24 pieces of each color.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The board starts off empty. Green goes first. For his first move, Green is not allowed to place any piece in the center space.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players take turns placing a piece on any empty space. They are attempting to form squares using their tokens to mark the 4 corners of the square.  Squares can be any size and any orientation. Which sometimes makes them difficult to perceive. It is possible for a single piece to complete the corners of several different squares.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After a player sets a piece, they check to see if any new squares were formed. They make note of how many and keep a running total. A player is given a reasonable time to count up all the new squares, and then the next player may take his turn. If a player spots any new squares after the other players sets a piece, that player loses those points.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After the last piece is set, the scores are tallied. High score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
